CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 7, 1953, pg. 6 reads: "YMCA "Ranch Bosses" - These five "ranch bosses," along with three other associates not shown, direct the strenuous campaigning of twenty-two "ranches," currently engaged in a city-wide Centre Avenue Branch YMCA membership "round-up." At the first report meeting, Monday night at the "Y," the division chefs gave encouraging reports and indicated that this year's goal of 1,800 members and $10,000 cash would be attained.  From left to right: The Rev. Clifton Morgan of "Dark Horse Ranch"; William Albea of the "Flying Red Horse Ranch"; Henry Adams Sr. of the "Circle Y Ranch"; John Holder of the "Flying Red Horse Ranch." and George Cain of the "Bar None Ranch." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Five YMCA membership campaign managers, including Rev. Clifton Morgan, William Albea, Henry Adams Sr., John Holder, and George Cain, gathered at desk in Centre Avenue YMCA
